@@TJvMruList.DeleteString@Integer
Description:
Use this method to delete an item in the list. Normally, you do not need to delete any string from the list, this is automatically done by Windows, but if you absolutely need to delete one, you can. This function has no correspondant for the data mode. if the index is out of bound or the list is inexistant, the function will return false.

