@@TJvMruList.DataType
Description:
This property is the type of data you want in your list. It can be either data or string. if the MRU list contains string, you will need to use the Addstring method, and AddData for a data MRU List.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMruList.MaxItems
Description:
This property is the number of items you want to see in the list. This doesn't mean it will always contain MaxItems elements, but it will contains maximum MaxItems. if the list contains MaxItems and if you add a Value, the oldest one is deleted, and the new one is inserted at the top of the list. The MRU has a similar aspect as a FIFO queue.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMruList.OnEnumData
Description:
This event is called when you have called the EnumItems, GetMostRecentItem or GetItem method and when the MRU list contains raw data. if the MRU list contains string, the event OnEnumText will be called.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMruList.OnEnumText
Description:
This event is called when you have called the EnumItems, GetMostRecentItem or GetItem method and when the MRU list contains strings. if the MRU list contains raw data, the event OnEnumData will be called.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMruList.RootKey
Description:
This property is the rootkey where to save/retrieve the MRU list. Habitually, you will use the default Value (hkCurrentUser).

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMruList.SubKey
Description:
This property is the registry key to use for the MRU List. This property is used with the rootkey property to determine the location of the MRU list in the registry. Each time you modify this Value, the MRU list is reCreated.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDataType
Description:
This is the type of data you want in the MRU List. It can be either string Values (dtstring) or raw data (dtBinary).

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
